706217f-a.text:
802 Park Place, south side, between Rogers and Nostrand Ave.  A view of the George B. Fisk's gardners cottage, still standing in 1925. (George B. Fisk in 1840 was a railroad agent, in 1844 was president of the Long Island R.R. He was also Alderman of the 9th Ward.)  Clove Road the road from Bedford to Flatbush, ran to the right of the house.
June 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
